cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.COMM, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1) cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the achievable rate regions and performance measures of a communication system. 
2) cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on the performance of a relay-based communication system. 
3) cs.SI (Signal Processing) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of the GQF scheme in a slow fading channel. 
4) cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) is a broad category that encompasses the topics covered in the paper. 
5) cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the expected sum rate (total throughput) as a performance measure.
